  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA89-kiḷavi">itu poruṇ muṟṟi maṟuttantā ṉeṉakkēṭṭa tōḻi talaivik kuraittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante, who had hear that he would be restored after having accomplished wealth, said to HER.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA89">
<l>            koṇṭa lāṟṟi viṇṭalaic ceṟīiyar</l>
<l>            tiraipitir kaṭuppa mukaṭukan tēṟi</l>
<l>            niraittunirai koṇṭa kamañcūṉ māmaḻai</l>
<l>            yaḻittuḷi kaḻippiya vaḻipeyaṟ kaṭainā</l>
<l>            ḷirumpaṉip paruvatta mayirkkā yuḻunti </l>
<l>            ṉakalilai yakala vīci yakalā</l>
<l>            talkalu malaikku nalkā vāṭai</l>
<l>            paruma yāṉai yayara vuyirttāṅ</l>
<l>            kiṉṉum varumē tōḻi vārā</l>
<l>            vaṉka ṇāḷarō ṭiyainta </l>
<l>            puṉkaṇ mālaiyum pulampumun tuṟuttē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>On the last days of successive(?) rains, when the dwindling drops</l>
<l rend="indent">of the fully pregnant clouds that formed an orderly row are spent,</l>
<l rend="indent2">having risen upwards to the top so that the spray of the waves is</l>
<l rend="indent4">spread(?),</l>
<l rend="indent3">while the heads are close to the sky, bearing the eastwind,</l>
<l>now also the ungranting north wind comes, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent3">sighing like an elephant that lowers itself to a seat,</l>
<l rend="indent2">that slaps, though it still abides, the black-gram with hairy unripe</l>
<l rend="indent2">fruits in the season of great dew, dashing [at it] incessantly</l>
<l rend="indent3">so that the wide leaves take off(?)</l>
<l rend="indent2">– bringing loneliness into dominance, at sorrowful evening too,</l>
<l rend="indent2">that was enjoyable with [our] strong man, who has not come.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
        </text>
